  "source": "[\\set.theoretic.natural.number]\nDescribes: n\nextends: n is \\set\nDocumented:\n. called: \"natural number\"\n. description: \"A natural number is an element of the set $\\omega$ of natural numbers. Each natural number is itself a set, and the natural number $n$ has exactly $n$ elements.\"\nId: \"0678dcc0-116f-4043-8f24-b033a4914f5e\"",
